      <div class="hgroup">
        <h1>Executive Brief — Quirk AI (Corporate)</h1>
        <p class="sub">On-premise corporate assistant improving speed, consistency, and compliance across 13 OEMs / 20 stores.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="meta">
      <span class="chip">Status: Pilot (Internal)</span>
      <span class="chip">Scope: BDC, Sales, Service, Parts, Marketing</span>
      <span class="chip">Privacy: On-prem isolation</span>
    </div>

    <h2>Why it matters (business outcomes)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Response speed:</b> reduce handle time for common tasks by <b>30–50%</b>.</li>
      <li><b>Consistency:</b> one brand voice, compliant across <b>13 OEMs / 20 stores</b>.</li>
      <li><b>Quality:</b> better lead follow-up, clearer repair notes, fewer escalations.</li>
      <li><b>Privacy:</b> on-premise isolation; PII redaction in logs.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Phase-1 scope</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Internal copilots for BDC, Internet/Sales, Service Writers, Parts, Marketing.</li>
      <li>Template bundles (email/SMS) + Department playbooks (SOPs).</li>
      <li>Read-only adapters to CRM/DMS (e.g., VIN Solutions).</li>
      <li>Voice pilots via Twilio → reverse proxy (Caddy) → OpenAI Realtime.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Out of scope (Phase-1)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Direct write-backs to DMS/CRM without review.</li>
      <li>Public model exposure; data remains private.</li>
      <li>Autonomous actions without human approval.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Governance & risk controls</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>System/meta prompts; guardrail language; test harness.</li>
      <li>On-premise reverse proxy; egress allow-list; TLS at the edge.</li>
      <li>PII redaction in logs; PR-based change management.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Timeline (indicative)</h2>
    <table class="table">
      <tr><th>Phase</th><th>Weeks</th><th>Outcomes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>P1</td><td>0–4</td><td>Internal copilots + templates; voice pilot path; security posture</td></tr>
      <tr><td>P2</td><td>5–12</td><td>Playbooks, automations; limited write-backs with approvals</td></tr>
      <tr><td>P3</td><td>13+</td><td>Reporting, A/B tests; broader integrations</td></tr>
    </table>

